	" and was released for a variety of systems during the mid-1980s including the SG-1000 in 1985. It was also ported to Sega System 1 arcade hardware by Sega. Gameplay is similar to the original game, but the levels are more maze-like. It features tweaks such as a lives system, minecarts, balloons and even a final Demon boss. Other than that, the plot is identical to the versions released for the Atari 2600.
